<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Phylogenetic relationships within Cantharellus species inferred from the combined nLSU (large subunit of the ribosome) and tef- 1 α (transcription elongation factor 1 - alpha) sequences, by maximum likelihood method and Bayesian inference. The new species are indicated in bold letters. Bootstrap scores (only values ≥ 70) and Bayesian Posterior Probabilities (only values ≥ 0.90) are indicated above branches." , "Figure 5. Cantharellus tabernensis (Herrera 131) a basidiospores b basidia c Terminal elements of the pileipellis d longitudinal section of pileipellis. Scale bars: 5 μm (a); 10 μm (b, c); 25 μm (d)." , "Figure 2. Basidiomes of Cantharellus species a, b C. veraecrucis (a Bandala 4505, holotype b Herrera 142) c, d C. parvoflavus (c Montoya 5423, holotype d Herrera 229) e, f C. tabernensis (e Herrera 120 f Herrera 131). Scale bars: 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545049" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545053" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545050" .

